   recently gained much attention. While some attempts have been made to
   explore the growth potential of the two policies separately, no
   empirical analysis has considered their joint contribution to regional
   growth. This paper identifies two types of development (measured as
   2008-2010 GDP growth) effects associated to smart policies: one,
   short-run, associated to urban smartness initiatives, and a second, long
