   (i.e. GHG emission and rising power demand), the smart microgrids
   including Renewable Energy Sources (RESs) based charging infrastructure
   are becoming the most viable paradigm. In this paper, two most emerging
   technologies belonging to smart cities i.e. xEVs and RESs based smart
   Microgrid has been covered. The xEVs part of the presented manuscript
   discusses the detailed study of rising advancement in xEVs charging
   infrastructure, enhancement in international standards for proper xEVs
   deployment, and state of art in the xEVs application such as the vehicle
   to grid (V2G) and vehicle to home (V2H). The second part of the
