Abstract = {{An Internet of Things' (IoT) connected society and system represents a
   tremendous paradigm shift. We present a framework for a decision-support
   system (DSS) that operates within the IoT ecosystem. The DSS leverages
   advanced analytics of electric smart meter (ESM) network
   communication-quality data to improve cost predictions for smart meter
   field operations and provide actionable decision recommendations
   regarding whether to send a technician to a customer location to resolve
   an ESM issue. The model is empirically evaluated using data sets from a
   commercial network. We demonstrate the efficiency of our approach with a
   complete Bayesian network prediction model and compare with three
   machine learning prediction model classifiers: 1) Naive Bayes; 2) random
   forest; and 3) decision tree. Results demonstrate that our approach
   generates statistically noteworthy estimations and that the DSS will
   improve the cost efficiency of ESM network operations and maintenance.}},
