Title = {{ADS-B System as a Useful Tool for Testing and Redrawing Noise Management
   Strategies at Pisa Airport}},
Journal = {{ACTA ACUSTICA UNITED WITH ACUSTICA}},
Year = {{2017}},
Volume = {{103}},
Number = {{4}},
Pages = {{543-551}},
Month = {{JUL-AUG}},
Abstract = {{Noise pollution can significantly limit the growth of the communities
   located nearby an airport. Pisa International Airport has recently
   presented its action plan, which includes both the construction of a
   runway link that increases the take-off run length and the introduction
   of the ICAO-A noise-abatement procedure. Nevertheless, the airport still
   needs to develop new strategies to ensure an effective noise reduction
   as a response to the growing aircraft traffic. This paper shows an
   innovative approach for managing airport noise on the closest urban
   areas based on the Automatic Dependent Surveillance-Broadcast (ADS-B)
   technology. ADS-B output data were used to track the flight departures
   with high data resolution and then to verify both the effectiveness of
   the action plan and the compliance with its provisions. A penetration
   gate was strategically set considering the departures towards the city.
   The vertical distribution of the traffic crossing the gate and the
   correlation between take-off conditions and noise-related events were
   investigated in order to establish rules for penalties due to the lack
   of compliance with the action plan requirements. The results confirmed
   that ADS-B system could be considered a smart tool producing
   cost-effective solutions for the airport noise management in urban
   areas, particularly when the radar tracks are not available.}},
