Abstract = {{Digital signature is an important cryptographic tool in the security and
   privacy of smart city. Certificateless signature has not only simplified
   certificate management of traditional public-key signature, but also
   solved the private key escrow problem of ID-based signature. Recently,
   Pang et al.'s proposed a certificateless signature scheme in the
   standard model. We find that their scheme is vulnerable to the attack of
   malicious but-passive KGC adversary. From the analysis of Pang et al.'s
   secure proof, we give a suggestion for the proof of certificateless
   signature, i.e., we cannot remain some possible trapdoor information for
   KGC. Then we propose a strongly secure certificateless signature scheme,
   and give the secure proof in standard model. Compared with Pang et al.'s
   and other certificateless signature scheme in standard model, our
   proposed scheme can resist attack of malicious-but-passive KGC
