Month = {{JUN}},
Abstract = {{Although the knowledge about place branding and place management is
   growing, there is a substantial gap in the understanding of place
   branding among professionals responsible for the management of town and
   city centres, including private-public partnership formats such as
   business improvement districts (BIDs). This exploratory study addresses
   this knowledge gap through in-depth interviews with key professionals in
   England, Wales, Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland. The
   results suggest that the strategic potential of place branding is
   negatively affected by a focus on operational thinking, which hinders
   innovation towards more holistic approaches to place management. Further
   quantitative research is needed to elaborate on these findings across
   the UK, Ireland and other countries to enhance the understanding of the
   uses and interpretations of place branding among town and city managers.}},
