   together with six mid-sized European cities. The main areas of focus
   have been evaluated based on the cities' priorities: transportation
   (both public and private) and consumers' perspectives on the use of
   smart electricity meters. The use of electric vehicles in Sweden, and a
   techno-economic evaluation of biogas-derived biomethane and electricity
   use in public transportation have been analyzed. The main conclusions
   show an overall higher efficiency for biogas-derived electricity use in
   electric buses; a need for higher consumer engagement through more
